            {
              "id": "CE-001",
              "name": "Toolscapableofsendingdatatoexternaldestinations",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Tools capable of sending data to external destinations"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "2 tool(s) have names suggesting they can send data externally. These tools could potentially be used by a manipulated AI agent to exfiltrate conversation context, system prompts, or user data to an attacker-controlled endpoint."
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "Restrict outbound tools to specific allowlisted destinations. Implement content filtering to prevent sensitive data from being included in outbound payloads. Require user confirmation for all data-sending operations.",
                "markdown": "**Remediation:** Restrict outbound tools to specific allowlisted destinations. Implement content filtering to prevent sensitive data from being included in outbound payloads. Require user confirmation for all data-sending operations."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "note"
              },
              "properties": {
                "severity": "LOW",
                "module": "context-extraction",
                "security-severity": "5.3",
                "tags": [
                  "security",
                  "mcp",
                  "context-extraction",
                  "CWE-200",
                  "NIST SP 800-171:3.1.3",
                  "SOC 2 TSC:CC6.5",
                  "OWASP ASVS:V7.4.1"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "CE-004",
              "name": "Toolswithusercontrolleddestinationparameters",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Tools with user-controlled destination parameters"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Tools accept destination parameters (to, recipient, endpoint, webhook_url) that allow AI agents to specify where data is sent. A prompt injection could redirect sensitive data to attacker-controlled endpoints."
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "Hardcode or allowlist permitted destinations. Never allow AI agents to specify arbitrary URLs, email addresses, or endpoints for outbound data.",
                "markdown": "**Remediation:** Hardcode or allowlist permitted destinations. Never allow AI agents to specify arbitrary URLs, email addresses, or endpoints for outbound data."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "warning"
              },
              "properties": {
                "severity": "MEDIUM",
                "module": "context-extraction",
                "security-severity": "5.3",
                "tags": [
                  "security",
                  "mcp",
                  "context-extraction",
                  "CWE-201",
                  "NIST SP 800-171:3.1.3",
                  "SOC 2 TSC:CC6.5",
                  "OWASP ASVS:V7.4.1"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "SSRF-001",
              "name": "ToolsacceptURLparameters",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Tools accept URL parameters"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "1 tool(s) accept URL parameters, which are potential SSRF vectors if not properly validated."
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "Implement URL allowlisting, block private IP ranges, and validate URL schemes (allow only https://).",
                "markdown": "**Remediation:** Implement URL allowlisting, block private IP ranges, and validate URL schemes (allow only https://)."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "note"
              },
              "properties": {
                "severity": "LOW",
                "module": "ssrf-detection",
                "tags": [
                  "security",
                  "mcp",
                  "ssrf-detection"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "AF-006-read_file",
              "name": "Noinputlengthlimitsontoolreadfile",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "No input length limits on tool \"read_file\""
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Tool \"read_file\" parameter \"path\" accepted oversized inputs (10k-ascii, 100k-ascii, 5k-unicode-skull) without returning validation errors. This may indicate missing input length validation, which can lead to denial-of-service or memory exhaustion attacks."
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "Enforce maximum input length limits on all string parameters. Return clear validation errors for inputs that exceed acceptable bounds. Consider rate limiting and request size limits at the transport level.",
                "markdown": "**Remediation:** Enforce maximum input length limits on all string parameters. Return clear validation errors for inputs that exceed acceptable bounds. Consider rate limiting and request size limits at the transport level."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "warning"
              },
              "properties": {
                "severity": "MEDIUM",
                "module": "active-fuzzer",
                "security-severity": "5.3",
                "tags": [
                  "security",
                  "mcp",
                  "active-fuzzer",
                  "CWE-400",
